Endo Agrees to Buy American Medical Systems for About $2.9 Billion in Cash

-- B y   J o A n n e   N o r t o n
-- 
2011-04-11T10:04:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/endo-agrees-to-buy-american-medical-systems-for-about-2-9-billion-in-cash.html
Endo Pharmaceuticals Holdings Inc. (ENDP) 
said it agreed to buy  American Medical Systems Holdings Inc. (AMMD)  for
$30 a share, or $2.9 billion in cash, which includes the
assumption and repayment of $312 million of AMS debt.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
JoAnne Norton at 
 jnorton@bloomberg.net  